Target: OntoCityToilets is an ontology developed for representing public toilets in a city.

Comment: Represents various amenities available within a city. Instances of this class include facilities and services such as toilets, parks, hospitals, schools, etc.
Label: Amenity

Comment: Represents public toilets within a city
Label: Toilet

Comment: Shows details on toilet pricing, including payment fees and currency information.
Label: price specification

Comment: Specifies the pricing details for a specific toilet.
Label: has fee

Comment: Indicates if an amenity has image.
Label: has image

Comment: Represents the unique identifier of an amenity.
Label: has ID

Comment: Indicates the operator or entity responsible for a particular amenity.
Label: has operator

Comment: Represents the name of the city.
Label: has name

Comment: Represents the price (fee) for the amenity.
Label: price

Comment: Represents the price currency for the amenity.
Label: price currency

Comment: Indicates the suitability of places or ways for wheelchair access and accommodation of individuals using mobility devices (e.g., walkers).
Label: has wheelchair

Comment: Indicates that a toilet is specifically designed for males.
Label: is for male

Comment: Indicates that a toilet is specifically designed for females.
Label: is for female
